title: For Sale:  walther model 4
location: New port richey, Tampa/St. Pete, Florida
postcontent:
Model 4, was introduced concurrently with the Model 3, in 1910.  It too was a blowback operated pistol chambered for the 7.65mm Browning.  It was larger than the earlier models, being of the size for which a holster might be  deemed necessary, but the longer grips and barrel improved the pistol's handling and pointing characteristics.  The Model 4  was the first Walther pistol to achieve notable commercial success, and many were used by police agencies as well as the German military during World War One.  The pistol has an elongated barrel bushing which serves the same purpose as that on the earlier pistols, but in addition, also carries the front sight.  Model 4's were manufactured between 1910 and 1918.  The Model 4 was 6" long and weighed about 18.5 ounces.  Magazine capacity was eight rounds. 
This is a very collectable handgun, it's the detectivs version, wich makes it very rare! $375obo. To purchase: 21 and FL resident with a clean record REDACTED

title: For Sale:  M1 Garand
postcontent: Up for sale is an excellent example of a hard to find complete correct as-issued M1 Rifle from WWII. Condition is overall excellent with over 95% original finish. Typical dings and wear in stock and finish wear on high points, but that's to be expected. No import marks, rebuild marks, repairs, cracks, or evidence of rebuilding, sanding, refinishing or restoring. 8/44 dated original Springfield Armory barrel has TE 0.0 and ME 0.0 and mirror bright sharp bore. No chrome at gas port and chamber in the white. Un-modified revision 9 curve side operating rod, lock-bar rear sights, and very nice SA/GAW cartouched stock with nice matching hanguards. No buggered screws or any signs rifle was played with. You would be hard pressed to find a better example of a very desirable as-issued WWII M1 rifle. A great addition to any M1 or US Martial collection.
